Benazir Bhutto, leader of the People's Democratic Party, on Thursday promised to end the 
"reactionary" legacy of late President Zia ul-Haq if she is elected.  Zia died in an August 17 
plane crash.

Ms. Bhutto is the 35-year old daughter of the late  Prime Minister Zulfikar Ali Bhutto, who was 
ousted in a 1977 coup and ordered hanged.  Her party is pitted against the nine-party Islamic 
Democratic Alliance, which says Ali Bhutto committed political murders, jailed his opponents, 
and denied a wide range of freedoms.  Ms. Bhutto has accused the Alliance and Zia loyalists of 
having a poor human rights record.</SUM>

<SUM
