About 50,000 people today marked the first anniversary of the death of President Mohammed 
Zia ul-Haq by holding an anti-government rally denouncing his successor, Benazir Bhutto.  Zia 
died in a plane crash August 17, 1988 which appeared to be sabotage.  He had seized power in a 
1977 coup ousting and executing Ms. Bhutto's father, Zulfikar Ali Bhutto.

Pakistani officials have blamed hundreds of terrorist attacks in recent years on Soviet-trained 
agents of Afghanistan's communist government.  Zia was a supporter of anti-communist Afghan 
guerrillas.

Zia loyalists accuse Benazir Bhutto of civilian dictatorship, being a traitor, and an agent of the 
Russians and Indians.</SUM>

<SUM
