A brief look at Benazir Bhutto's career:

April 10, 1986--returns from exile, resurrects Pakistan People's Party.

August 17, 1988--Pakistan's military ruler dies in plane crash.

November 16, 1988--Ms. Bhutto's party emerges as country's largest.

December 2, 1988--takes oath as Prime Minister.

December 31, 1988--foreign policy triumph by meeting Indian Prime Minister Rajiv Gandhi.

May 5, 1989--squabbling in provinces interferes with public works program.

December 2, 1989--corruption charges start to be leveled regularly against cabinet ministers and 
Bhutto family members.

August 5, 1990--removed as prime minister, accused of corruption, nepotism, and political 
ineptitude.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d088"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
