SUMMARIZER="G">

Benazir Bhutto charged Wednesday that powerful army generals forced her ouster as prime 
minister.  She warned that the army will take over in a few weeks.  Military and government 
officials denied the charges, insisting that general elections will be held October 24.  They said 
Bhutto, her family and close aides will be barred from leaving the country pending investigations 
of corruption.

Bhutto's aides said the investigations might be used to prevent her from taking part in the 
elections.  She said "major differences" developed over the army chief of staff's demands to 
crack down on urban violence in her home province.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d088"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
