SUMMARIZER="G">

The National Assembly held a session inn Islamabad today at which the Prime Minister Benazir 
Bhutto welcomed the opposition's decision to end the boycott of the Assembly.  She invited the 
opposition and other political party leaders for discussion on economic issues.  Regarding her 
challenge to the opposition for submitting resignations, she said she was confident they would 
not.

She said strict action will be taken against those responsible for the parliament building fire.  The 
situation of terrorist training in the Sindh province will be tackled politically and Karachi's 
problems will be resolved by providing drinking water, more electricity, transport and hospitals.</SUM>
